<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 10:11AM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Cherokee and
southern Crawford Counties through 1045 AM CDT...
At 1010 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Treece, or near Columbus, moving north at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pittsburg...                      Baxter Springs...
Frontenac...                      Columbus...
Galena...                         Cherokee...
Weir...                           Lowell...
Sherman...                        Scammon...
Chicopee...                       Mccune...
West Mineral...                   Roseland...
Neutral...                        Melrose...
Beulah...                         Riverton...
Carona...                         Hallowell...
This includes Interstate 44 near mile marker 0.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
